data.title: IWC Chairs & Vice-chairs
data.text:
The Chair and Vice-chair are elected from among the Commissioners and usually serve for four years, first as Vice-chair for two years, and then as Chair.

The current Chair is Amadou Telivel Diallo of the Republic of Guinea and the current Vice-chair is Dr Nick Gales of Australia. Both were elected into office at the Commission meeting in October 2022.

Amadou Telivel Diallo, Republic of Guinea, current IWC Chair

Dr Nick Gales, Australia, current IWC Vice-chair

List of Previous Chairs

The names and national government of IWC Chairs and Vice-chairs from 1949 to the present day are listed below. An additional column shows the Meeting Chair which, for a variety of reasons, has occasionally differed from the Annual/Biennial Chair.
